<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Dala's playground (Posts about spacemacs)</title><link>https://dalanicolai.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://dalanicolai.github.io/categories/spacemacs.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents © 2020 &lt;a href="mailto:dalanicolai@gmail.com"&gt;Daniel Nicolai&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Tue, 01 Sep 2020 15:16:15 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>A simple Emacs helm example</title><link>https://dalanicolai.github.io/posts/a-simple-emacs-helm-example/</link><dc:creator>Daniel Nicolai</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;
Although I recommend Ivy over Helm for most people, because Ivy's use and
documentation is much more approachable, there might be some time that you can
not avoid using Helm. I find Helm's documentation quite cryptic, with very few
examples. Therefore here follow two simple examples to help you out quickly.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;defun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;helm-print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;interactive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;helm&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;:sources&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;helm-build-sync-source&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;"Name"&lt;/span&gt;
		     &lt;span class="nv"&gt;:candidates&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
		     &lt;span class="nv"&gt;:action&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;((&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;"print"&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;lambda &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
					     &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)))))))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>spacemacs</category><guid>https://dalanicolai.github.io/posts/a-simple-emacs-helm-example/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 01 Sep 2020 15:05:32 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Spacemacs Robot framework layer</title><link>https://dalanicolai.github.io/posts/spacemacs-robot-framework-layer/</link><dc:creator>Daniel Nicolai</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;
This week support for the &lt;a href="https://github.com/tomi/vscode-rf-language-server"&gt;Robot Framework Intellisense&lt;/a&gt; language server was added
to Emacs's lsp-mode.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
For easy installation a spacemacs layer that also uses the
&lt;a href="https://github.com/dougm/robot-mode"&gt;robot-mode package&lt;/a&gt; by Doug MacEachern can be found &lt;a href="https://github.com/dalanicolai/robot-framework-layer"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;</description><category>robot framework</category><category>spacemacs</category><guid>https://dalanicolai.github.io/posts/spacemacs-robot-framework-layer/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2020 15:33:18 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>